J.H. Whitney Acquires TIDI Products, LLC | Business Wire


























































J.H. Whitney Acquires TIDI Products, LLC






July 17, 2012 05:17 PM Eastern Daylight Time



NEW CANAAN, Conn.--(BUSINESS WIRE)--J.H. Whitney Capital Partners, LLC (“J.H. Whitney”), a leading 
      middle-market private equity firm, announced today that it acquired TIDI 
      Products, LLC (“TIDI” or the “Company”).
    


      Based in Neenah, WI, TIDI is a leading provider of disposable infection 
      prevention products used by physicians, dentists and in acute care 
      settings. The Company’s core products include patient gowns and draping, 
      dental bibs and towels, tray covers, equipment covers and sheaths, and 
      barrier products. With over 40 years of experience in the industry, TIDI 
      enjoys a leading market position and strong relationships with the 
      nation’s leading healthcare distributors.
    

      “TIDI has worked hard to develop an industry-leading platform that 
      delivers great service and value to our customers,” said Kevin McNamara, 
      CEO and President of TIDI. “We look forward to partnering with J.H. 
      Whitney and believe that together we can enhance the next level of 
      growth for TIDI.”
    

      “TIDI products represent the first line of defense in the fight against 
      healthcare acquired infections – a key priority in today’s healthcare 
      environment,” said Brian Cherry, Managing Director at J.H. Whitney. “We 
      have partnered with an experienced management team with an exceptional 
      track record of customer service and financial performance. Together we 
      are committed to the continued growth of TIDI.”
    

      About TIDI Products, LLC:
    

      TIDI is a leading manufacturer of single use infection control products 
      for medical and dental distribution. Its products include patient exam 
      gowns, examination table paper, dental bibs, gauze sponges and 
      thermometer sheaths. TIDI customers include numerous leading healthcare 
      and dental product distributors.
    

      About J.H. Whitney:
    

      Established in 1946 by the industrialist and philanthropist, John Hay 
      “Jock” Whitney, J.H. Whitney was one of the first U.S. private equity 
      firms and is often credited with pioneering the development of the 
      private equity industry. Today, J.H. Whitney remains privately owned by 
      its investing professionals and focuses on providing private equity 
      capital to small and middle market companies with strong growth 
      prospects in a number of industries including consumer, healthcare, 
      specialty manufacturing and business services. For more information, 
      please visit www.whitney.com.
    


Contacts

      J.H. Whitney Capital Partners, LLCMichael C. Salvator, Managing 
      Director203-716-6100contact@whitney.com













Contacts

      J.H. Whitney Capital Partners, LLCMichael C. Salvator, Managing 
      Director203-716-6100contact@whitney.com







 
 

 






